  "prompt": "What is the best app to learn English?",
  "response": "The best app to learn English can vary depending on your learning style, goals, and preferences. Here are some highly regarded options:\n\n1. **Duolingo**: A popular app that uses gamification to help users learn vocabulary and grammar through bite-sized lessons.\n\n2. **Rosetta Stone**: Known for its immersive approach, it focuses on teaching English through context and visual cues without translating.\n\n3. **Babbel**: Offers structured courses focusing on conversation skills, grammar, and vocabulary, with lessons that adapt to your skill level.\n\n4. **Busuu**: Combines self-study with a community aspect, allowing you to practice with native speakers and get feedback on your exercises.\n\n5. **Memrise**: Uses spaced repetition and mnemonic techniques to aid vocabulary retention, often incorporating videos of native speakers.\n\n6. **HelloTalk**: A language exchange app where you can chat with native English speakers and they can learn your language in return.\n\n7. **Lingoda**: Provides online classes with qualified teachers, focusing on real-life conversations and structured lessons.\n\n8. **FluentU**: Uses real-world videos like movie clips and music videos to teach English in context, helping with listening skills.\n\nConsider trying a few of these to see which one aligns best with your learning style!",
